          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-3889 osc: Allow lock to be canceled at ENQ time",
        "message": "LU-3889 osc: Allow lock to be canceled at ENQ time\n\nA cl_lock can be canceled when it's in CLS_ENQUEUED state.\nWe can't unuse this kind of lock in lov_lock_unuse() because\nit will bring this lock into CLS_NEW state and then confuse\nosc_lock_upcall().\n\nAdd a regression test case by Alexander Boyko.\n\nBackported from: 13079de3417ce41ce485b2bdad36834e2f6e6e15\n\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander_boyko@xyratex.com>\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I56954eefa226b3b4da389f182879200a92be402c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_4"
    }
  },
